I usually get so excited for a new year. Lots of new opportunities, a fresh start, etc. But the last month or so I’ve been stuck in such a funk & I just feel like I’m just repeating the motions. 3 months postpartum I felt like everything clicked with going from 1-2 kids. We were in a routine, I felt proud of myself, my anxiety settled, & I was starting to feel like “me again”. I went back to work in November and it’s been really tough since. I can’t seem to figure out a new routine that balances working full time, motherhood, cleaning, relationships, self care, etc. It seems nearly impossible for me but everyone around me can do it. I feel drained, not a good enough mom, wife, or friend. “Why can’t I have the energy to take my kids to do fun things?” “Why are my friends mad at me?” “Why do I feel like I can’t leave to do anything that’s for myself?”. It never ends. I just can’t figure it out *yet*. Posting this to reflect back on next year because I’ve been stuck here before & I know once I get “out” it feels so good 🫶 So if you’re stuck too..heres to getting out of bed today, making an apt with a therapist, trying to get some fresh air, and taking a deep breath. #postpartum #motherhood #momtruth #motherhoodintheraw #workingmom #newyear

Trying to decide between a flat or inclined walking pad? You can’t go wrong with either but here’s what I think after trying both: 

-If you’re looking for a good everyday walking pad to get a good distance in without any effort go with the flat one. 
-If you want a challenge, more of a workout, and to sweat go with the incline. Small but mighty! It’s deff challenging but a good way to sweat & work your booty while working. 

I’m walking on @egofit_ergonomics F1 (flat) and M1-Pro(incline). Code HS30OFF saves you $30! Full review on www.Haleysimao.com
